attachments.title: Covid-19: New Zealand cases mapped and charted, April 1
attachments.text: The third in our new series of charts, graphics and data visualisations by Chris McDowall, covering the Covid-19 epidemic within New Zealand. We’ll publish the latest set each day on The Spinoff. This work is entirely funded by the generosity of The Spinoff Members Information about confirmed
attachments.fallback: The Spinoff: Covid-19: New Zealand cases mapped and charted, April 1

[April 4th, 2020 8:36 AM] eshetu: Hello everyone, 
If any one of you need an aggregated data for covid-19 cases in Ethiopia, we have built a kind of proxy off of the API from the PMO and you can find them here:
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_regions> … returns aggregated data for all regions in Ethiopia
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_regions>/<REG_CODE> … returns aggregated data for specific region … you can get the code from the above end point as part of individual regions node.
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_genders> … returns aggregated data by gender
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_genders/><GEN_CODE> … returns aggregated data for specific gender type

You can see these in action here : <https://www.sewasew.com/covid>
Will be building more of these in the days to come and will make sure to share them here.

Cheers,

Hello everyone, 
If any one of you need an aggregated data for covid-19 cases in Ethiopia, we have built a kind of proxy off of the API from the PMO and you can find them here:
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_regions> … returns aggregated data for all regions in Ethiopia
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_regions>/<REG_CODE> … returns aggregated data for specific region … you can get the code from the above end point as part of individual regions node.
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_genders> … returns aggregated data by gender
<https://www.sewasew.com/api/c_genders/><GEN_CODE> … returns aggregated data for specific gender type

You can see these in action here : <https://www.sewasew.com/covid>
Will be building more of these in the days to come and will make sure to share them here.

Cheers,
